We selected 26 samples of human plasma. HAI titers against A/California/07/2009 ranged from 5 to 1280, organized in low (HAI 5-50), middle (HAI 160-202), and high (HAI 320-1280) groups (Table 1
). Opsonization (presented as binding intensity) to uninfected cells was consistently low. For infected cells, we observed a MFI of 5000 or higher for opsonization of antigen in the 1:200 dilutions in all plasma except for Low10, High1, and High8 (Fig. 4
A). In 1:1000 or higher dilutions, opsonization tapered off dramatically in cells treated with the low titer and middle titer plasma. This phenomenon occurred to a lesser extent with the middle titer group. We observed higher opsonization in the 1:200 dilutions for most of the samples in the high titer group, and continued to see significant opsonization in the higher dilutions with the exception of High1 and High8 plasmas, which consistently showed diminished opsonization akin to the samples with low titer (Fig. 4A).
